The Adamawa State House of Assembly has concluded the screening of all the 23 commissioner nominees forwarded to it by Governor Ahmadu Umaru Fintiri. The Assembly confirmed this at its sitting on Wednesday. The final confirmation of the nominees at the Wednesday sitting followed completion of the screening exercise with three remaining nominees: Alhaji Bappa Dalhatu Isa from Ganye, Lami Patrick from Gombi and Adamu Titus from Shelleng. After reconvening from the Committee of the whole, the Speaker of the House, Aminu Iya Abbas, presented the 23 commissioner nominees. He named them one after the other and the lawmakers confirmed them respectively. The speaker thereafter directed the Clerk of the House to communicate the resolution to the Executive arm for further action. Governor Ahmadu Umaru Fintiri had forwarded the 23 nominees to the House of Assembly on the 23rd of last month. The House screened 11 on Monday and nine on Tuesday. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.